---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import FourInARow from '../../components/game/FourInARow.tsx';
---

<Layout title="Lab">
  <section class="min-h-screen pt-24 pb-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <!-- Lab Header -->
      <div class="mb-20 reveal">
        <h1 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-4xl text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-50 mb-4">Lab</h1>
        <p class="text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 max-w-xl leading-relaxed">
          Prototypes exploring how AI can make people genuinely more capable.
          Each one starts from a research question and ships as something you can actually use.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Projects -->
      <div class="space-y-20">

        <!-- Nightshift: AI Experiment Design Platform -->
        <article class="reveal">
          <div class="mb-8">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100">Nightshift</h2>
              <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-0.5 bg-violet-50 dark:bg-violet-950/40 text-violet-700 dark:text-violet-400 rounded-full border border-violet-200 dark:border-violet-500/20">
                Full-stack app
              </span>
            </div>
            <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300 mb-4 max-w-xl leading-relaxed text-base">
              A platform for cognitive scientists, psychologists, behavioral researchers &mdash; anyone who designs experiments with human participants &mdash; to prototype, simulate, and analyze studies in minutes instead of weeks.
            </p>
            <p class="text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 mb-5 max-w-xl leading-relaxed text-sm">
              Simulations are grounded in two layers. A <strong class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300">parametric engine</strong> encodes established cognitive mechanisms from the literature &mdash; latent factor models calibrated to published factor loadings, BFS-computed construal probabilities, Big Five trait covariance &mdash; so the fast path produces psychologically plausible data, not random noise. An <strong class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300">LLM-as-participant</strong> mode adds process-level richness: identity-driven personas where behavior emerges naturally from who the simulated person <em>is</em> (a phone-checking 19-year-old, a methodical retiree), producing chain-of-thought traces and strategy descriptions. Both are validated against published findings (Ho et al. Nature 2022, Lin &amp; Ma NComms).
            </p>

            <!-- Key capabilities -->
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-3 mb-6">
              <div class="rounded-xl p-4 border border-stone-200 dark:border-stone-800 bg-white/50 dark:bg-stone-900/30">
                <p class="text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-accent-600 dark:text-accent-400 mb-1.5">Design</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400">Conversational AI agent proposes experiment variants with three distinct research personas</p>
              </div>
              <div class="rounded-xl p-4 border border-stone-200 dark:border-stone-800 bg-white/50 dark:bg-stone-900/30">
                <p class="text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-accent-600 dark:text-accent-400 mb-1.5">Simulate</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400">Parametric engine grounded in cognitive mechanisms, or LLM personas for process-level data &mdash; calibrated to published results</p>
              </div>
              <div class="rounded-xl p-4 border border-stone-200 dark:border-stone-800 bg-white/50 dark:bg-stone-900/30">
                <p class="text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-accent-600 dark:text-accent-400 mb-1.5">Analyze</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400">Opus-powered analysis chat with heatmaps, factor analysis, and peer-review simulation</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-5">
              <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-1 bg-stone-100 dark:bg-stone-800/50 text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 rounded-full">React 19</span>
              <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-1 bg-stone-100 dark:bg-stone-800/50 text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 rounded-full">TypeScript</span>
              <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-1 bg-stone-100 dark:bg-stone-800/50 text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 rounded-full">Framer Motion</span>
              <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-1 bg-stone-100 dark:bg-stone-800/50 text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 rounded-full">Claude API</span>
              <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-1 bg-stone-100 dark:bg-stone-800/50 text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 rounded-full">Vercel</span>
              <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-1 bg-stone-100 dark:bg-stone-800/50 text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 rounded-full">Cognitive Science</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-6">
              <a href="https://nightshift-ten.vercel.app/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
                class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-sm font-medium text-accent-600 dark:text-accent-400 hover:text-accent-700 dark:hover:text-accent-300 transition-colors duration-300 group">
                Try it live
                <svg class="w-3 h-3 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform duration-300" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3"></path></svg>
              </a>
              <a href="https://github.com/daisilin/nightshift" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
                class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-sm text-accent-600 dark:text-accent-400 hover:text-accent-700 dark:hover:text-accent-300 transition-colors duration-300 group">
                GitHub
                <svg class="w-3 h-3 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform duration-300" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3"></path></svg>
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Nightshift feature highlights -->
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-stone-200 dark:border-stone-800 p-6 bg-white/50 dark:bg-stone-900/30">
            <p class="text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-stone-400 dark:text-stone-500 mb-4">Why this matters</p>
            <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400 leading-relaxed">
              <p class="pl-7 relative before:content-['✦'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-accent-400/60 dark:before:text-accent-500/40">
                Parametric simulations encode real cognitive mechanisms &mdash; latent factor models, construal probabilities from path salience, trait covariance structures &mdash; not just statistical noise
              </p>
              <p class="pl-7 relative before:content-['✦'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-accent-400/60 dark:before:text-accent-500/40">
                LLM personas add process-level richness: behavior emerges from identity (age, motivation, cognitive style), producing chain-of-thought traces researchers can inspect
              </p>
              <p class="pl-7 relative before:content-['✦'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-accent-400/60 dark:before:text-accent-500/40">
                Construal effect replicates at 85% of published human data (Ho et al. Nature 2022) &mdash; and the tool is honest about where it diverges and why
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- Mode: Adaptive AI Interface -->
        <article class="reveal">
          <div class="mb-8">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <h2 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100">Mode</h2>
              <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-0.5 bg-violet-50 dark:bg-violet-950/40 text-violet-700 dark:text-violet-400 rounded-full border border-violet-200 dark:border-violet-500/20">
                Prototype
              </span>
            </div>
            <p class="text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 mb-5 max-w-xl leading-relaxed">
              An adaptive AI interface that changes how it guides you based on your working style.
              Built around a cognitive science insight: people approach tasks with systematically different strategies,
              and interfaces should adapt to that &mdash; not force everyone into the same workflow.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-5">
              <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-1 bg-stone-100 dark:bg-stone-800/50 text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 rounded-full">React</span>
              <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-1 bg-stone-100 dark:bg-stone-800/50 text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 rounded-full">TypeScript</span>
              <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-1 bg-stone-100 dark:bg-stone-800/50 text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 rounded-full">Tailwind CSS</span>
              <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-1 bg-stone-100 dark:bg-stone-800/50 text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 rounded-full">Framer Motion</span>
              <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-1 bg-stone-100 dark:bg-stone-800/50 text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 rounded-full">Cognitive Science</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-6">
              <a href="https://github.com/daisilin/mode" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
                class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-sm text-accent-600 dark:text-accent-400 hover:text-accent-700 dark:hover:text-accent-300 transition-colors duration-300 group">
                GitHub
                <svg class="w-3 h-3 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform duration-300" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3"></path></svg>
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Mode preview cards -->
          <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-3">
            {[
              { name: 'Planner', color: '#3B82F6', desc: 'Structure first' },
              { name: 'Explorer', color: '#8B5CF6', desc: 'Follow curiosity' },
              { name: 'Driver', color: '#F97316', desc: 'Move fast' },
              { name: 'Coach', color: '#22C55E', desc: 'Step by step' },
            ].map(mode => (
              <div
                class="rounded-xl p-4 border transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-0.5"
                style={`background: ${mode.color}08; border-color: ${mode.color}18;`}
              >
                <h3 class="text-sm font-medium mb-1" style={`color: ${mode.color}`}>{mode.name}</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-stone-500">{mode.desc}</p>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- Four-in-a-Row -->
        <article class="reveal">
          <div class="mb-8">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <h2 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100">Four-in-a-Row vs AI</h2>
              <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-0.5 bg-sky-50 dark:bg-sky-950/40 text-sky-700 dark:text-sky-400 rounded-full border border-sky-200 dark:border-sky-500/20">
                Interactive
              </span>
            </div>
            <p class="text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 mb-5 max-w-xl leading-relaxed">
              Play the game from our NeurIPS 2024 paper on AI planning. This 4x9 board variant
              (free placement, connect 4 to win) was used to study how AlphaZero and humans develop
              different planning strategies. The AI uses minimax search — can you beat it?
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-5">
              <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-1 bg-stone-100 dark:bg-stone-800/50 text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 rounded-full">Game AI</span>
              <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-1 bg-stone-100 dark:bg-stone-800/50 text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 rounded-full">Minimax</span>
              <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-1 bg-stone-100 dark:bg-stone-800/50 text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 rounded-full">NeurIPS 2024</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- The actual game -->
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-stone-200 dark:border-stone-800 p-4 sm:p-8 bg-white dark:bg-stone-900/30">
            <FourInARow client:load />
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- Research Context -->
        <article class="border-t border-stone-200 dark:border-stone-800 pt-16 reveal">
          <h2 class="section-label mb-8">The thread connecting all of this</h2>
          <p class="text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 max-w-xl leading-relaxed mb-4">
            My PhD studied how people develop skill at complex tasks &mdash; running large-scale experiments with thousands of participants across 9 planning games, identifying what makes some people get dramatically better while others plateau.
          </p>
          <p class="text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 max-w-xl leading-relaxed mb-8">
            That research shapes everything I build. Nightshift simulates how diverse humans would experience an experiment. Mode adapts its interface to your cognitive style. The RL work at Amazon trains agents that collaborate with humans, not replace them. The core question: <em class="text-stone-700 dark:text-stone-300">how do we design AI that makes people progressively more capable?</em>
          </p>
          <div class="flex gap-6">
            <a href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=PYIV3fcAAAAJ" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
              class="text-sm text-stone-500 hover:text-stone-900 dark:hover:text-stone-200 link-underline transition-colors duration-300">
              Google Scholar
            </a>
            <a href="https://github.com/daisilin" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
              class="text-sm text-stone-500 hover:text-stone-900 dark:hover:text-stone-200 link-underline transition-colors duration-300">
              GitHub
            </a>
          </div>
        </article>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
